Package: mc-server
Version: 0.2.0
Architecture: all
Maintainer: Dylan Bulmer <dylan@bulmer.dev>
Depends: curl, jq, unzip
Recommends: rsync, mc-rcon
Section: admin
Priority: optional
Homepage: https://apt.bulmer.dev
Description: Minecraft server lifecycle manager
 mc-server manages a single Minecraft server instance on bare-metal or inside
 VMs/LXC containers. It supports Vanilla (default), Paper, Fabric, and NeoForge
 server types and provides commands for installation, upgrades, backups, restores,
 and systemd lifecycle management. Supports Modrinth .mrpack modpack files.
 .
 Java version (8, 17, 21, or 25) is selected automatically based on the
 requested Minecraft version, including Mojang's new 26.x versioning scheme.
 .
 RCON is disabled by default. Install mc-rcon to enable the RCON console and
 enable the 'mc rcon' subcommand.
